  "prompt": "How did Kakashi get the Sharingan?",
  "response": "Kakashi received his Sharingan from his dying teammate Obito Uchiha during the Third Shinobi World War. When Kakashi was a young ninja, he and his team (including Obito and Rin) were on a mission. They were trapped behind enemy lines, and Obito saved Kakashi's life when he was about to be crushed by a falling boulder. During this rescue, Obito was severely injured and about to die. Before his death, he gave Kakashi his left Sharingan eye as a gift, replacing Kakashi's damaged left eye. This is why Kakashi is known as \"Kakashi of the Sharingan\" or \"Copy Ninja Kakashi,\" despite not being an Uchiha clan member by birth. Since he is not a natural Uchiha, using the Sharingan constantly drains his chakra, which is why he typically keeps it covered with his headband when not in use.",
